  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Author of a conventional, one-distich funerary epigram on Sappho (Anth. Pal. 7,16
    inclusion in the Garland of Philippus [32] highly doubtful). The rarity of the name suggests identification with the 
    grammarian P. of Bithynium, freedman of Epaphroditus and secretary to Nero (Steph. Byz. s.v. Βιθύνιον)..." 
    Albiani, Maria Grazia (Bologna). "Pinytus." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2009. Brill Online. Tufts University Library. 21 October 2009</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Smith's Dictionary of Greek and Roman Biography and Mythology, Vol 3, 1867, p. 370: "Pi'nytus, 
    an epigrammatic poet, the author of an epitaph on Sappho, consisting of a single distich, in the Greek Anthology...
    Nothing more is known of him, unless he be the grammarian of Bithynium...."</mads:note>
